ZH: 风吹过树叶，树叶发出轻微的作响。
EN: The wind blew through the leaves, and they made a slight rustling sound.

ZH: 这个机器运行时会发出巨大的作响。
EN: This machine makes a loud noise when it is running.

ZH: 大雨砸在窗户上，发出噼里啪啦的作响。
EN: The heavy rain smashed against the windows, making a pitter-patter sound.

ZH: 听到大海的潮水声，我感到非常平静，它们作响时非常美妙。
EN: Hearing the sound of the ocean waves, I felt very peaceful, they made a beautiful sound.

ZH: 四处飞舞的彩蝶，翅膀洒出微弱的作响。
EN: The fluttering butterflies around made a faint sound with their wings.

ZH: 她高跟鞋在地板上发出清脆的作响。
EN: Her high heels made a crisp sound on the floor.

ZH: 我轻轻挤压那个玩具，它发出了吱吱作响的声音。
EN: I squeezed the toy gently, and it made a squeaky sound.

ZH: 那只猫在吃东西时会作响。
EN: The cat makes a noise when it is eating.

ZH: 孩子们用手拍打那只小鼓，鼓皮发出了咚咚的作响。
EN: The children beat the little drum with their hands, and the drumhead made a thudding sound.

ZH: 水流过石头，发出了潺潺的作响。
EN: The water flowed over the stones, making a gurgling sound.

ZH: 电视在播放时会发出类似嘀嘀的作响。
EN: The television makes a beeping sound when it is playing.

ZH: 骑自行车时，轮胎在路面上作响。
EN: When riding a bicycle, the tires make a sound on the road.

ZH: 刀子在切割食材时发出刺耳的作响。
EN: The knife makes a harsh sound when cutting ingredients.

ZH: 铁门开启时发出脆响作响。
EN: The iron gate makes a sharp sound when it opens.

ZH: 就在我旁边，手机收到信息的时候，会作响。
EN: Right next to me, the phone makes a sound when receiving a message.

ZH: 地铁进站时会作响，提醒乘客即将停靠。
EN: The subway makes a sound when it arrives at the station, reminding passengers that it will stop soon.

ZH: 雪花落在地面上，发出绵绵的作响。
EN: Snowflakes fall onto the ground, making a soft sound.

ZH: 气球被扎破时，会发出砰的一声作响。
EN: When a balloon is punctured, it makes a loud popping sound.

ZH: 电灯泡在熄灭时会作响。
EN: The light bulb makes a sound when it goes out.

ZH: 防盗器在商店门口发出警报作响。
EN: The anti-theft alarm at the store entrance makes a loud ringing sound.

ZH: 小鸟在枝头跳跃时，发出了嗒嗒的作响。
EN: The little birds make a chirping sound when hopping on the branches.
